Section 3 -- License Conditions.

Your exercise of the Licensed Rights is expressly made subject to the
following conditions.

a. Attribution.

   If You Share the Licensed Material (including in modified form), You must:

   1. retain the following if it is supplied by the Licensor with the
      Licensed Material:

      i. identification of the creator(s) of the Licensed Material and any
         others designated to receive attribution, in any reasonable manner
         requested by the Licensor (including by pseudonym if designated);

   2. provide a link back to this Public License and to the material and
      indicate if changes were made to the material; and

   3. indicate the Licensed Material is licensed under this Public License,
      and include the text of, or the URI to, this Public License.

   4. satisfy the conditions in Section 3(a)(1) in a reasonable manner,
      which may include linking to or otherwise making available a copy of
      the material with the same License Conditions.

For the avoidance of doubt, the requirement in Section 3(a)(1)(A)(ii) does
not apply to the extent that the Licensor's credit is not reasonably
practicable due to the nature of the material or the use.

b. ShareAlike.

In addition to the conditions in Section 3(a), if You Share Adapted
Material, You also must meet the following conditions:

1. You must include the text of, or the URI to, this Public License and
   the Adapter's License You apply to the Adapted Material. You must meet
   the conditions in Section 3(a) in a reasonable manner.

2. The Adapter's License You apply to Adapted Material must be a Creative
   Commons license with the same License Elements, this version or later,
